<br>
A few patches ago, VI decided to shafe mages and wizzies, this time... hardcore. The spell, Elemental Armor, a very nice FR &amp; CR buff, no longer stacks with Circle of Seasons, a nice druid FR and CR buff.<br>
<br>
i was talking with a GM about it and he said it was because of class balancing. he told me that we can get our resists insanely high as opposed to melee types.<br>
<br>
i replyed telling him that was what made the classes balanced. us mages are supposed to get better resists because on big mobs, that aoe, we do marginally less damage than the melee folks.<br>
<br>
i would like to get this changed for the good of our class. it makes elemental armor useless and makes class balancing a little more one sided, fairing the melees...<br>
<br>
<br>
Aelzrith Neverest,<br>
Arch Mage of Luclin<br>
